  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of anxiety?",
  "response": "Anxiety can manifest in various ways, affecting both the mind and body. Common symptoms include:\n\n1. **Emotional Symptoms:**\n   - Persistent worry or excessive fears.\n   - Feeling tense or on edge.\n   - Overwhelming feelings of apprehension or dread.\n   - Irritability or restlessness.\n\n2. **Cognitive Symptoms:**\n   - Racing thoughts.\n   - Difficulty concentrating or focusing.\n   - Anticipating the worst-case scenario.\n   - Memory problems.\n\n3. **Physical Symptoms:**\n   - Increased heart rate or palpitations.\n   - Sweating or trembling.\n   - Shortness of breath or rapid breathing.\n   - Fatigue or weakness.\n   - Nausea or gastrointestinal issues.\n   - Dizziness or lightheadedness.\n   - Muscle tension or headaches.\n\n4. **Behavioral Symptoms:**\n   - Avoidance of feared situations or activities.\n   - Compulsive behaviors as a way to relieve anxiety.\n\nIt's important to note that experiencing some of these symptoms occasionally is normal, especially in response to stress. However, if these symptoms persist or interfere with daily life, it may be indicative of an anxiety disorder, and seeking help from a healthcare professional could be beneficial.",
